{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778981362584,"sessionID":"ses_1cc74bc03ffej3HRdIj8PFimMZ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_8wYMktofhUxlp4PuuqzjUBtj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Updated `life cycle` (UBERON:0000104) and `life cycle stage` (UBERON:0000105) to be subclasses of `BFO:0000015 ! process`, matching the request in this issue. I left the separate `life cycle temporal boundary` branch unchanged, since the issue discussion treated that as a follow-up/COB alignment question rather than part of the requested Uberon edit.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+This change addresses issue `#3464` by moving the two requested life-cycle terms from `UBERON:0000000 ! processual entity` to `BFO:0000015 ! process`.\n+\n+Updated terms:\n+- `UBERON:0000104` `life cycle`\n+- `UBERON:0000105` `life cycle stage`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue requested positioning these occurrent classes under `process` for COB compatibility.\n+- The current ontology already uses imported BFO classes directly, so reparenting these terms to `BFO:0000015` is the minimal change that satisfies the request.\n+- I did not modify `UBERON:0035943` `life cycle temporal boundary` or its children, because the issue discussion treated those terms as a separate modeling question and did not ask for a concrete Uberon change to that branch.\n+\n+Checks completed:\n+- Read the imported issue context and comments to confirm scope.\n+- Inspected the current stanzas for `UBERON:0000104`, `UBERON:0000105`, `UBERON:0000000`, and `UBERON:0035943`.\n+- Confirmed the final diff only changes the two intended `is_a` assertions.\n+- Checked the terms out via `obo-checkout.pl`, edited the checked-out stanzas, and checked them back in with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n+- Reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert -i src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo -f obo -o src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n+- Verified the resulting stanzas in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` now use `is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process`.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Addressed in PR #<NN>.\n+\n+Updated `life cycle` (UBERON:0000104) and `life cycle stage` (UBERON:0000105) to be subclasses of `BFO:0000015 ! process`, matching the request in this issue. I left the separate `life cycle temporal boundary` branch unchanged, since the issue discussion treated that as a follow-up/COB alignment question rather than part of the requested Uberon edit.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@\n+This change addresses issue `#3464` by moving the two requested life-cycle terms from `UBERON:0000000 ! processual entity` to `BFO:0000015 ! process`.\n+\n+Updated terms:\n+- `UBERON:0000104` `life cycle`\n+- `UBERON:0000105` `life cycle stage`\n+\n+Rationale:\n+- The issue requested positioning these occurrent classes under `process` for COB compatibility.\n+- The current ontology already uses imported BFO classes directly, so reparenting these terms to `BFO:0000015` is the minimal change that satisfies the request.\n+- I did not modify `UBERON:0035943` `life cycle temporal boundary` or its children, because the issue discussion treated those terms as a separate modeling questio